{{notability|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox military person |name=Joachim Meißner |birth_date={{birth date|1911|10|15|df=y}} |death_date={{death date and age|1944|7|25|1911|10|15|df=y}} |birth_place=[[Kożuchów|Freystadt in Schlesien]] |death_place=[[Saint-Lô]], [[France]] |image= |image_size= |caption= |nickname= |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch={{Luftwaffe}} |serviceyears=?–1944 |rank=''[[Hauptmann]]'' |commands= |unit=[[Luftlande-Sturm-Regiment|Fallschirmjäger-Sturm-Abteilung "Koch"]] |battles=[[World War II]] *[[Battle of Fort Eben-Emael]] *[[Battle of Crete]] *[[Siege of Leningrad]] *[[Operation Overlord|Battle of Normandy]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] |laterwork=}}
'''Joachim Meißner''' (15 October 1911 – 25 July 1944) was a highly decorated [[Hauptmann]] in the [[Fallschirmjäger]] during [[World War II]]. He was also a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.
==Awards and decorations== * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class (12 May 1940)<ref name="Thomas & Wegmann p179">Thomas & Wegmann 1986, p. 179.</ref> ** 1st Class (13 May 1940)<ref name="Thomas & Wegmann p179"/> * [[Eastern Front Medal]] (4 July 1942)<ref name="Thomas & Wegmann p179"/> * [[Ground Assault Badge of the Luftwaffe]] (26 October 1942)<ref name="Thomas & Wegmann p179"/> * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 12 May 1940 as ''[[Leutnant]]'' of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]] and deputy leader of Sturmgruppe "Eisen" (Assault Group "Iron") in Fallschirmjäger-Sturm-Abteilung "Koch"<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 251.</ref> * [[Cuff title|Armband Crete]]
